    <h1>Kinlog Support</h1>
    <p class="meta"><strong>App:</strong> Kinlog</p>
    <p class="meta"><strong>Last updated:</strong> [April 2026]</p>
    <p>Need help with Kinlog? This page covers common questions, troubleshooting, and how to contact support.</p>
    <h2>Contact Support</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:[lianshao@outlook.jp]">[lianshao@outlook.jp]</a></p>
      <p><strong>Response time:</strong> Usually within 2-3 business days.</p>
      <p><strong>Please include:</strong> iOS version, device model, app version, and steps to reproduce the issue.</p>
    </div>
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <h3>How do I add a person?</h3>
    <p>Open the People section and tap <strong>Add New Person</strong>.</p>
    <h3>How do I attach logs to a contact?</h3>
    <p>When creating or editing a log entry, select one or more people in the <strong>Who was involved</strong> area.</p>
    <h3>How does contact sharing work?</h3>
    <p>You can share selected contact information from inside the app. Only data you explicitly choose to share is exported.</p>
    <h3>How do follow-up reminders work?</h3>
    <p>Enable follow-up on a log, then choose reminder timing. Make sure Notifications are allowed in iOS Settings.</p>
    <h3>How do I use app lock / Face ID?</h3>
    <p>Go to Settings in Kinlog and enable App Lock. If Face ID is available, iOS will prompt you for permission.</p>
    <h3>How do I back up my data?</h3>
    <p>Use Kinlog's backup/export options. If iCloud features are enabled, data may also sync through your Apple account.</p>
    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
    <h3>Notifications are not arriving</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Check iOS Settings &gt; Notifications &gt; Kinlog and allow alerts.</li>
      <li>Confirm reminder time is set in the app.</li>
      <li>Disable Focus mode or check allowed apps.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Location is missing on logs</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Check iOS Settings &gt; Privacy &amp; Security &gt; Location Services &gt; Kinlog.</li>
      <li>Allow location access if you want place context.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>App is not unlocking with Face ID</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Verify Face ID is enabled for Kinlog in iOS Settings.</li>
      <li>Restart the app and try again.</li>
      <li>If needed, disable and re-enable App Lock in Kinlog settings.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Data &amp; Privacy</h2>
    <p>For details about how we handle data, please read our Privacy Policy:</p>
    <p><a href="../privacy.html">View Privacy Policy (English)</a></p>
    <h2>Compatibility</h2>
    <p>Kinlog requires a supported iPhone or iPad running a recent iOS/iPadOS version available on the App Store listing.</p>
    <h2>Report a Bug or Request a Feature</h2>
